<tr>       <td style=\"width: 46px;\"><strong>length</strong></td>       <td style=\"width: 92px;\">object</td>       <td style=\"width: 81px;\">NA</td>       <td style=\"width: 444px; text-align: justify;\">Type:&nbsp;<a href=\"/api-reference/duty-and-tax-calculator#get-started-section/reference-data%unit\">unit</a>. Length of the item per item unit of measure.</td>       <td style=\"width: 89px; text-align: center;\">O</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td style=\"width: 46px;\"><strong>height</strong></td>       <td style=\"width: 92px;\">object</td>       <td style=\"width: 81px;\">NA</td>       <td style=\"width: 444px; text-align: justify;\">Type:&nbsp;<a href=\"/api-reference/duty-and-tax-calculator#get-started-section/reference-data%unit\">unit</a>. Height of the item per item unit of measure.</td>       <td style=\"width: 89px; text-align: center;\">O</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td style=\"width: 46px;\"><strong>volume</strong></td>       <td style=\"width: 92px;\">object</td>       <td style=\"width: 81px;\">NA</td>       <td style=\"width: 444px; text-align: justify;\">Type:&nbsp;<a href=\"/api-reference/duty-and-tax-calculator#get-started-section/reference-data%unit\">unit</a>. Volume of the item per item unit of measure. Note: If volume is not null AND length width and height are populated, volume takes precedence for volume calculation.</td>       <td style=\"width: 89px; text-align: center;\">O</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td style=\"width: 46px;\"><strong>area</strong></td>       <td style=\"width: 92px;\">object</td>       <td style=\"width: 81px;\">NA</td>       <td style=\"width: 444px; text-align: justify;\">Type:Type&nbsp;<a href=\"/api-reference/duty-and-tax-calculator#get-started-section/reference-data%unit\">unit</a>. Area of the item per item unit of measure.</td>       <td style=\"width: 89px; text-align: center;\">O</td>     </tr>   </tbody> </table>  <p>M/O/C indicates whether a datatype/property is Mandatory/Optional/Conditional</p>  <p>&nbsp;</p>  <h6>RESPONSE PARAMETERS</h6>  <p>The DTC response will echo back all parmeters that were input in the request, plus the following:</p>  <table style=\"width: 927px;\">   <thead>     <tr>       <th style=\"text-align: left; width: 141px;\">Element Name</th>       <th style=\"text-align: left; width: 128px;\">Type</th>       <th style=\"text-align: left; width: 81px;\">Length</th>       <th style=\"text-align: left; width: 491px;\">Description</th>       <th class=\"text-align-center\" style=\"width: 83px;\">       <center>M/O/C</center>       </th>     </tr>   </thead>   <tbody>     <tr>       <td style=\"width: 141px;\"><strong>quoteID</strong></td>       <td style=\"width: 128px;\">string</td>       <td style=\"width: 81px;\">36</td>       <td style=\"width: 491px;\">Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for the quote. This is generated internally by DHL eCommerce.</td>       <td style=\"text-align: center; width: 83px;\">M</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td style=\"width: 141px;\"><strong>info</strong></td>       <td style=\"width: 128px;\">array of objects</td>       <td style=\"width: 81px;\">NA</td>       <td style=\"width: 491px;\">Type:&nbsp;<a href=\"/api-reference/duty-and-tax-calculator#get-started-section/reference-data%info\">info</a>. Informational messages returned from the DTC engine regarding the request. For example:<br />       <br />       “info” : [<br />       {\"message\" : “Item ABC fee EXCISE could not be calculated due to …” },<br />       {\"message\" : “Item DEF fee EXCISE could not be calculated due to …” }<br />       ]</td>       <td style=\"text-align: center; width: 83px;\">O</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td style=\"width: 141px;\"><strong>feeTotals</strong></td>       <td style=\"width: 128px;\">array of objects</td>       <td style=\"width: 81px;\">NA</td>       <td style=\"width: 491px;\">Type:&nbsp;<a href=\"/api-reference/duty-and-tax-calculator#get-started-section/reference-data%fee\">fee</a>. Details all fees being incurred for the shipment, including package and item fees. For example:<br />       <br />       “feeTotals” : [<br />       { \"name\": \"HMF\", \"currency\": \"USD\", \"value\": 1.00},<br />       { \"name\": \"MPF\", \"currency\": \"USD\", \"value\": 4.25},<br />       { \"name\": \"DUTY\", \"currency\": \"USD\", \"value\": 22.56 },<br />       { \"name\": \"VAT\", \"currency\": \"USD\", \"value\": 3.66 }<br />       ]</td>       <td style=\"text-align: center; width: 83px;\">M</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td style=\"width: 141px;\"><strong>packageFees</strong></td>       <td style=\"width: 128px;\">array of objects</td>       <td style=\"width: 81px;\">NA</td>       <td style=\"width: 491px;\">Type:&nbsp;<a href=\"/api-reference/duty-and-tax-calculator#get-started-section/reference-data%fee\">fee</a>. Details all fees being incurred at the package level. For example:<br />       <br />       packageFees\" : [<br />       { \"name\": \"HMF\", \"currency\": \"USD\", \"value\": 1.00},<br />       { \"name\": \"MPF\", \"currency\": \"USD\", \"value\": 4.25}<br />       ]</td>       <td style=\"text-align: center; width: 83px;\">M</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td style=\"width: 141px;\"><strong>hsCodeApplied</strong></td>       <td style=\"width: 128px;\">string</td>       <td style=\"width: 81px;\">20</td>       <td style=\"width: 491px;\">Harmonized Schedule Code. This is the HS Code that was used for calculation of duties and taxes and may be different than the HS Code provided in the request, due to pricing strategy. If HS Code calculation required use of Default Duty Rates, then this field will indicate \"000000\". This element appears within the customsDetails block.</td>       <td style=\"text-align: center; width: 83px;\">M</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td style=\"width: 141px;\"><strong>customsNotes</strong></td>       <td style=\"width: 128px;\">string</td>       <td style=\"width: 81px;\">4000</td>       <td style=\"width: 491px;\">Customs notes, if any, regarding shipment of the item. This element, if present, appears in the customsDetail block.</td>       <td style=\"text-align: center; width: 83px;\">O</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td style=\"width: 141px;\"><strong>itemFees</strong></td>       <td style=\"width: 128px;\">array of objects</td>       <td style=\"width: 81px;\">NA</td>       <td style=\"width: 491px;\">Type:&nbsp;<a href=\"/api-reference/duty-and-tax-calculator#get-started-section/reference-data%fee\">fee</a>. The fee name, currency type and value of the fee being returned for the item. This object appears in the customsDetail block. For example:<br />       <br />       “itemFees” : [<br />       { \"name\": \"HMF\", \"currency\": \"USD\", \"value\": 1.00},<br />       { \"name\": \"MPF\", \"currency\": \"USD\", \"value\": 4.25 },<br />       { \"name\": \"DUTY\", \"currency\": \"USD\", \"value\": 12.75 },<br />       { \"name\": \"FREIGHT\", \"currency\": \"USD\", \"value\": 5.00}<br />       ]</td>       <td style=\"text-align: center; width: 83px;\">M</td>     </tr>   </tbody> </table>
    # @param accept
    # @param content_type
    # @param body
    # @param [Hash] opts the optional parameters
    # @option opts [String] :id
    # @return [RequestQuoteresponse]
    def flc_v1_quote_post(accept, content_type, body, opts = {})
      data, _status_code, _headers = flc_v1_quote_post_with_http_info(accept, content_type, body, opts)
      data
    end

    # Request Quote
    # &lt;h6&gt;REQUEST PARAMETERS&lt;/h6&gt;  &lt;p&gt;An DTC API Request can contain the elements detailed below:&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;table style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 930px;\&quot;&gt;   &lt;thead&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;th style&#x3D;\&quot;text-align: left; width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;Element Name&lt;/th&gt;       &lt;th style&#x3D;\&quot;text-align: left; width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;Type&lt;/th&gt;       &lt;th style&#x3D;\&quot;text-align: left; width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;Length&lt;/th&gt;       &lt;th style&#x3D;\&quot;text-align: left; width: 444px;\&quot;&gt;Description&lt;/th&gt;       &lt;th class&#x3D;\&quot;text-align-center\&quot; style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px;\&quot;&gt;       &lt;center&gt;M/O/C&lt;/center&gt;       &lt;/th&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;   &lt;/thead&gt;   &lt;tbody&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;pickupAccount&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;string&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;30&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;DHL assigned Customer Account number&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;M&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;itemSeller&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;string&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;30&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;Name of the item seller/merchant that is associated to the pickup account number. If provided, it must be a valid item seller that can be validated by DHL eCommerce.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;pricingStrategy&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;string&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;7&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;Pricing / Cost strategy.&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       EXACT - indicating there must be an exact match to an HS Code so that exact duty rates can be derived. If the pricing strategy is EXACT, and the system cannot find an exact HS Code match, the system will return an error of INVALID HS CODE:&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;HS CODE&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       For the pricing strategies of MAXIMUM, MINIMUM, and AVERAGE, the system returns the duty rate based on the number of HS digits of the input HS Code it can match to HS codes in the trade data – that is, EXACT, 6, 4, or 2 digits.&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       MAXIMUM - indicating the maximum duty rate found within the tariff data for the given HS Code will be used.&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       MINIMUM - indicating the minimum duty rate found within the tariff data for the given HS Code will be used.&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       AVERAGE - indicating the average duty rate found with the tariff data for the given HS Code sill be used.&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       If no pricingStrategy is provided in the request, fully landed cost will be calculated based on the EXACT strategy.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;senderAddress&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;object&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;NA&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;Type:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href&#x3D;\&quot;/api-reference/duty-and-tax-calculator#get-started-section/reference-data%address\&quot;&gt;address&lt;/a&gt;. Object detailing the sender’s address. The only field in the object that is required is the Country. Be aware that the country of the senderAddress must not be the same as the country of the consigneeAddress.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;M&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;consigneeAddress&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;object&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;NA&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;Type:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href&#x3D;\&quot;/api-reference/duty-and-tax-calculator#get-started-section/reference-data%address\&quot;&gt;address&lt;/a&gt;. Object detailing the consignee’s address. The only field in the object that is required is the Country, however for accurate fee calculations, some destination countries do require State. Be aware that the country of the consigneeAddress must not be the same as the country of the senderAddress.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;M&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;packageDetails&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;object&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;NA&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;Container/List object populated with pertinent details regarding the shipment&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;M&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;freightCharge&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;object&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;NA&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;Type:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href&#x3D;\&quot;/api-reference/duty-and-tax-calculator#get-started-section/reference-data%monetary-value\&quot;&gt;monetaryValue&lt;/a&gt;. Object detailing the total freight charges for the order/shipment.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;insuranceCharge&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;object&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;NA&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;Type:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href&#x3D;\&quot;/api-reference/duty-and-tax-calculator#get-started-section/reference-data%monetary-value\&quot;&gt;monetaryValue&lt;/a&gt;. Object detailing the total insurance charges for the order/shipment.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;outputCurrency&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;string&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;3&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;ISO currency code for the currency type that will be used in the DTC response. All monetary values that are provided in the response will be converted to this currency.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;M&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;clearanceMode&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;string&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;20&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;Identifies the mode of customs clearance. Valid clearance modes are: Post, Courier, or blank (null). May be required in order to accurately calculate duties, taxes, and fees.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;endUse&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;string&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;10&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;Defines whether the order is for personal and business use. Valid options are: &#39;Personal’, &#39;Business’, and ‘Gifts.’ May be required in order to accurately calculate duties, taxes, and fees.&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       If endUse is not provided, the request should not fail, but de minimis may not be calculated since endUse is required for the de minimis formula. This could result in higher than necessary fees being calculated.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;transportMode&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;string&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;20&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;Identifies the method of transport for the shipment. This may impact duty and tax rates. Valid methods of transport: AIR, OCEAN, GROUND.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;customsDetails&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;array&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;NA&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;Container/list array populated with details for all commodities in the shipment&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;M&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;itemId&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;string&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;20&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;Item identifier, which may be internal to the seller, such as a SKU. Must be unique within the shipment.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;M&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;hsCode&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;string&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;20&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;Harmonized Schedule Code for the item. May be 2, 4, 6 or full classification. No special characters may appear in the HS Code string, except for hyphens, spaces and periods. If hyphens, spaces or periods appear in the string, these will be stripped out by the system.&amp;nbsp;A leading zero may precede some HS codes, for example 01-09. Acceptable characters are 0-9, A through Z, a through z, hyphens, periods, spaces and blanks. The first two characters of the HS Code must be numeric. If the hsCode element is blank or contains spaces (for example “” or \&quot; “, \&quot; \&quot;), the system will consider this as no HS Code being provided. If no HS Code is provided, or no valid HS Code is provided, default duty rates shall be returned as derived from agreed-to Customer configuration Data.&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       Valid Examples:&lt;br /&gt;       “”&lt;br /&gt;       \&quot; \&quot;&lt;br /&gt;       “12”&lt;br /&gt;       “1231.23”&lt;br /&gt;       \&quot; 12312”&lt;br /&gt;       “1231-23 \&quot;&lt;br /&gt;       \&quot; 12324 \&quot;&lt;br /&gt;       “12ABCD”&lt;br /&gt;       “12-123-AFDF”&lt;br /&gt;       “12.123.AFDF”&lt;br /&gt;       \&quot; 12-123.AFDF \&quot;&lt;br /&gt;       \&quot;12 -\&quot;&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       Invalid Examples:&lt;br /&gt;       “AA”&lt;br /&gt;       “1AA”&lt;br /&gt;       \&quot; - \&quot;&lt;br /&gt;       \&quot; . \&quot;&lt;br /&gt;       \&quot; . 1234”&lt;br /&gt;       “12$#@Q”&lt;br /&gt;       “12$#@Q”&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;skuNumber&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;string&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;50&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;FOR FUTURE USE: Stock Keeping Unit number assigned to the product. Used for auto-classification purposes only.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;productIdentifiers&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;object&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;NA&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;FOR FUTURE USE: Type:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href&#x3D;\&quot;/api-reference/duty-and-tax-calculator#get-started-section/reference-data%product-identifier\&quot;&gt;productIdentifiers&lt;/a&gt;. List of one or more product identifiers.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;productCategory&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;string&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;50&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;FOR FUTURE USE: Top level classification for the item’s category. For example, Electronics, Apparel, etc. Required for auto-classification.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;itemShortDescription&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;string&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;75&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;FOR FUTURE USE: Short description of the item. For example, Men’s Stay Cool Oxford Shirt. Required for auto-classification.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;itemDescription&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;string&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;200&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;FOR FUTURE USE: Long description of the product. For example, Men’s Stay Cool Slim Fit Oxford Shirt Broad Collar&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;size&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;string&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;10&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;FOR FUTURE USE: Describes the size of the item. For example, S, M, L, XL, XXL, etc… Required for auto-classification if item is apparel&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;gender&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;string&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;10&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;FOR FUTURE USE: Gender is used to determine product segments. For example, Male, Female, Unisex. M, F, etc. Required for auto-classification if item is apparel.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ageGroup&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;string&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;10&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;FOR FUTURE USE: Used to define the age group the item is created for. For example:&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       “newborn” - for ages up to 3 months old&lt;br /&gt;       “infant” - for ages 3-12 months&lt;br /&gt;       “toddler” - for ages 1-5 years&lt;br /&gt;       “kids” - for ages 5-13 years&lt;br /&gt;       “adult” - for teens or older.&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       Used for auto-classification purposes only.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;color&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;string&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;10&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;FOR FUTURE USE: The color of the item, fabric, dyes, etc.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;style&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;string&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;20&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;FOR FUTURE USE: Style references a certain product characteristic of apparel. For example, Slim, Tapered Polo, etc. Required for auto-classification if item is apparel.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;composition&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;array of string&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;NA&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;FOR FUTURE USE: Describes the makeup or material used. For example, {85% cotton, 15% polyester}. Required for auto-classification if item is apparel.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;condition&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;string&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;20&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;FOR FUTURE USE: Identifies the condition of the product. For example:&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       “new”&lt;br /&gt;       “used”&lt;br /&gt;       “refurbished”&lt;br /&gt;       “antique”&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       Use for auto-classification purposes only.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;countryOfOrigin&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;string&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;2&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;Two letter ISO Country Code for the commodity’s country of origin. Based on the ISO 3166-1 alpha 2 standard.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;qualifiesForPreferentialTariffs&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;boolean&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;NA&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;Many countries have preferential tariffs in place with other countries providing for discounted duty rates. These goods must meet certain criteria in order to claim preferential rates of duty. It cannot be assumed that if an item has a country of origin from a country with a preferential tariff thta the goods automatically qualify. Therefore the merchant must specifically indicate that the commodity qualifies for such preferential rates by setting this flag to true. Valid inputs are:&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       - true&lt;br /&gt;       - false&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       If not provided in the request, the system defaults to false.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;itemQuantity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;object&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;NA&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;Type:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href&#x3D;\&quot;/api-reference/duty-and-tax-calculator#get-started-section/reference-data%unit\&quot;&gt;unit&lt;/a&gt;. Quantity and quantity unit of measure of the item. A minimum quantity of ‘1’ is required&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;M&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;itemValue&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;object&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;NA&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;Type:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href&#x3D;\&quot;/api-reference/duty-and-tax-calculator#get-started-section/reference-data%monetary-value\&quot;&gt;monetaryValue&lt;/a&gt;. The total price for which the merchant is selling the item. This value is used for customs purposes. Note: When the system calculates total value for purposes of fee calculation, the system will utilize the itemValue multipled by the itemQuantity value. For example, if itemValue is $10.00 USD and itemQuanty is 5 DOZ, the system will multiple 10 X 5 to derive the product of $50.00 USD.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;M&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;itemFreight&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;object&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;NA&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;Type:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href&#x3D;\&quot;/api-reference/duty-and-tax-calculator#get-started-section/reference-data%monetary-value\&quot;&gt;monetaryValue&lt;/a&gt;. Freight cost for shipping the item. If provided, this value will be utilized when determining duties and taxes for certain countries. Note: itemFreight must be populated for all items in the request, otherwise it will not be used in duty and tax calculation; instead package level freightCharge will be utilized, prorated across all items in the request. Additionally, if itemFreight is provided, the sum total of all itemFreights must equal the package level freightCharge value, otherwise freightCharge will be prorated across all items.&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       When prorating package level freightCharge across all items in the requet, the system utilizes the following method: freightCharge / total itemQuantiy. For example,&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       freightCharge &#x3D; 600&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       Item-1 Quantity &#x3D; 5 DOZ&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       Item-2 Quantity &#x3D; 5 PCS&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       Total Quantity &#x3D; 5 + 5 &#x3D; 10&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       Freight Per Item &#x3D; freightCharge / Total Quantity&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       &amp;gt;&#x3D;&amp;gt; 600 / 10&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       &#x3D;&amp;gt; 60&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;itemInsurance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;object&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;NA&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;Type:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href&#x3D;\&quot;/api-reference/duty-and-tax-calculator#get-started-section/reference-data%monetary-value\&quot;&gt;monetaryValue&lt;/a&gt;. Insurance cost for the item. If provided, this value will be utilized when determining duties and taxes when CIF is required. Note: itemInsurance must be populated for all items in the request, otherwise it will not be used in duty and tax calculation; instead package level insuranceCharge will be utilized, prorated across all items in the request. Additionally, if itemInsurance is provided, the sum total of all itemInsurance must equal the package level insuranceCharge value, otherwise insuranceCharge will be prorated across all items.&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       When prorating package level insuranceCharge across all items in the request, the system utilizes the following method: insuranceCharge / total itemQuantiy. For example,&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       insuranceCharge &#x3D; 600&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       Item 1 Quantity &#x3D; 5 DOZ&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       Item-2 Quantity &#x3D; 5 PCS&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       Total Quantity &#x3D; 5 + 5 &#x3D; 10&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       Freight Per Item &#x3D; insuranceCharge / Total Quantity&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       &#x3D;&amp;gt; 600 / 10&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       &#x3D;&amp;gt; 60&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;weight&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;object&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;NA&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;Type:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href&#x3D;\&quot;/api-reference/duty-and-tax-calculator#get-started-section/reference-data%unit\&quot;&gt;unit&lt;/a&gt;. Weight of the item per identified item unit of measure. For example, if the request indicates an itemQuantiy of 5 DOZ, the weight tendered in the request should be for 1 DOZ.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;width&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;object&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;NA&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;Type:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href&#x3D;\&quot;/api-reference/duty-and-tax-calculator#get-started-section/reference-data%unit\&quot;&gt;unit&lt;/a&gt;. Width of the item per item unit of measure.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;length&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;object&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;NA&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;Type:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href&#x3D;\&quot;/api-reference/duty-and-tax-calculator#get-started-section/reference-data%unit\&quot;&gt;unit&lt;/a&gt;. Length of the item per item unit of measure.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;height&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;object&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;NA&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;Type:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href&#x3D;\&quot;/api-reference/duty-and-tax-calculator#get-started-section/reference-data%unit\&quot;&gt;unit&lt;/a&gt;. Height of the item per item unit of measure.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;volume&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;object&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;NA&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;Type:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href&#x3D;\&quot;/api-reference/duty-and-tax-calculator#get-started-section/reference-data%unit\&quot;&gt;unit&lt;/a&gt;. Volume of the item per item unit of measure. Note: If volume is not null AND length width and height are populated, volume takes precedence for volume calculation.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 46px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;area&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 92px;\&quot;&gt;object&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;NA&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 444px; text-align: justify;\&quot;&gt;Type:Type&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href&#x3D;\&quot;/api-reference/duty-and-tax-calculator#get-started-section/reference-data%unit\&quot;&gt;unit&lt;/a&gt;. Area of the item per item unit of measure.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 89px; text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;   &lt;/tbody&gt; &lt;/table&gt;  &lt;p&gt;M/O/C indicates whether a datatype/property is Mandatory/Optional/Conditional&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;h6&gt;RESPONSE PARAMETERS&lt;/h6&gt;  &lt;p&gt;The DTC response will echo back all parmeters that were input in the request, plus the following:&lt;/p&gt;  &lt;table style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 927px;\&quot;&gt;   &lt;thead&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;th style&#x3D;\&quot;text-align: left; width: 141px;\&quot;&gt;Element Name&lt;/th&gt;       &lt;th style&#x3D;\&quot;text-align: left; width: 128px;\&quot;&gt;Type&lt;/th&gt;       &lt;th style&#x3D;\&quot;text-align: left; width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;Length&lt;/th&gt;       &lt;th style&#x3D;\&quot;text-align: left; width: 491px;\&quot;&gt;Description&lt;/th&gt;       &lt;th class&#x3D;\&quot;text-align-center\&quot; style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 83px;\&quot;&gt;       &lt;center&gt;M/O/C&lt;/center&gt;       &lt;/th&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;   &lt;/thead&gt;   &lt;tbody&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 141px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;quoteID&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 128px;\&quot;&gt;string&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;36&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 491px;\&quot;&gt;Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for the quote. This is generated internally by DHL eCommerce.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;text-align: center; width: 83px;\&quot;&gt;M&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 141px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;info&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 128px;\&quot;&gt;array of objects&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;NA&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 491px;\&quot;&gt;Type:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href&#x3D;\&quot;/api-reference/duty-and-tax-calculator#get-started-section/reference-data%info\&quot;&gt;info&lt;/a&gt;. Informational messages returned from the DTC engine regarding the request. For example:&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       “info” : [&lt;br /&gt;       {\&quot;message\&quot; : “Item ABC fee EXCISE could not be calculated due to …” },&lt;br /&gt;       {\&quot;message\&quot; : “Item DEF fee EXCISE could not be calculated due to …” }&lt;br /&gt;       ]&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;text-align: center; width: 83px;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 141px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;feeTotals&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 128px;\&quot;&gt;array of objects&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;NA&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 491px;\&quot;&gt;Type:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href&#x3D;\&quot;/api-reference/duty-and-tax-calculator#get-started-section/reference-data%fee\&quot;&gt;fee&lt;/a&gt;. Details all fees being incurred for the shipment, including package and item fees. For example:&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       “feeTotals” : [&lt;br /&gt;       { \&quot;name\&quot;: \&quot;HMF\&quot;, \&quot;currency\&quot;: \&quot;USD\&quot;, \&quot;value\&quot;: 1.00},&lt;br /&gt;       { \&quot;name\&quot;: \&quot;MPF\&quot;, \&quot;currency\&quot;: \&quot;USD\&quot;, \&quot;value\&quot;: 4.25},&lt;br /&gt;       { \&quot;name\&quot;: \&quot;DUTY\&quot;, \&quot;currency\&quot;: \&quot;USD\&quot;, \&quot;value\&quot;: 22.56 },&lt;br /&gt;       { \&quot;name\&quot;: \&quot;VAT\&quot;, \&quot;currency\&quot;: \&quot;USD\&quot;, \&quot;value\&quot;: 3.66 }&lt;br /&gt;       ]&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;text-align: center; width: 83px;\&quot;&gt;M&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 141px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;packageFees&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 128px;\&quot;&gt;array of objects&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;NA&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 491px;\&quot;&gt;Type:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href&#x3D;\&quot;/api-reference/duty-and-tax-calculator#get-started-section/reference-data%fee\&quot;&gt;fee&lt;/a&gt;. Details all fees being incurred at the package level. For example:&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       packageFees\&quot; : [&lt;br /&gt;       { \&quot;name\&quot;: \&quot;HMF\&quot;, \&quot;currency\&quot;: \&quot;USD\&quot;, \&quot;value\&quot;: 1.00},&lt;br /&gt;       { \&quot;name\&quot;: \&quot;MPF\&quot;, \&quot;currency\&quot;: \&quot;USD\&quot;, \&quot;value\&quot;: 4.25}&lt;br /&gt;       ]&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;text-align: center; width: 83px;\&quot;&gt;M&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 141px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;hsCodeApplied&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 128px;\&quot;&gt;string&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;20&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 491px;\&quot;&gt;Harmonized Schedule Code. This is the HS Code that was used for calculation of duties and taxes and may be different than the HS Code provided in the request, due to pricing strategy. If HS Code calculation required use of Default Duty Rates, then this field will indicate \&quot;000000\&quot;. This element appears within the customsDetails block.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;text-align: center; width: 83px;\&quot;&gt;M&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 141px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;customsNotes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 128px;\&quot;&gt;string&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;4000&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 491px;\&quot;&gt;Customs notes, if any, regarding shipment of the item. This element, if present, appears in the customsDetail block.&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;text-align: center; width: 83px;\&quot;&gt;O&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     &lt;tr&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 141px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;itemFees&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 128px;\&quot;&gt;array of objects&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 81px;\&quot;&gt;NA&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;width: 491px;\&quot;&gt;Type:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href&#x3D;\&quot;/api-reference/duty-and-tax-calculator#get-started-section/reference-data%fee\&quot;&gt;fee&lt;/a&gt;. The fee name, currency type and value of the fee being returned for the item. This object appears in the customsDetail block. For example:&lt;br /&gt;       &lt;br /&gt;       “itemFees” : [&lt;br /&gt;       { \&quot;name\&quot;: \&quot;HMF\&quot;, \&quot;currency\&quot;: \&quot;USD\&quot;, \&quot;value\&quot;: 1.00},&lt;br /&gt;       { \&quot;name\&quot;: \&quot;MPF\&quot;, \&quot;currency\&quot;: \&quot;USD\&quot;, \&quot;value\&quot;: 4.25 },&lt;br /&gt;       { \&quot;name\&quot;: \&quot;DUTY\&quot;, \&quot;currency\&quot;: \&quot;USD\&quot;, \&quot;value\&quot;: 12.75 },&lt;br /&gt;       { \&quot;name\&quot;: \&quot;FREIGHT\&quot;, \&quot;currency\&quot;: \&quot;USD\&quot;, \&quot;value\&quot;: 5.00}&lt;br /&gt;       ]&lt;/td&gt;       &lt;td style&#x3D;\&quot;text-align: center; width: 83px;\&quot;&gt;M&lt;/td&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;   &lt;/tbody&gt; &lt;/table&gt;
